    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-06-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="612"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Tyler</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 30.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    telegram of the 18th ultimo, in which you reported the arrest of Mir Ghaffar,
                    the leader of the gang who murdered Mr. Labarre and his servant.</p>
                <p>The Department expects the legation to continue to be perseveringly attentive to
                    this case, to the end that full justice may be meted out to the participators in
                    the crime.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
